Package com.aevi.printing

This package provides classes for printing functionality in third-party applications.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    OnPrinterQueryCallback
    Interface definition for a callback to be invoked when querying the list of available printers.
    PrintCallbackListener
    The PrintCallbackListener interface can be used to register a listener for a print event.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    PrinterSettings
    Contains information such as name, DPI and paper width for a specific PrinterSettings on the Device.
    PrintJobStateChangedEvent
    Contains the data associated with the state changed of a print job.
    PrintService
    The PrintService class is the main interface for executing Print Request.
    PrintServiceProvider
    The PrintServiceProvider class gives an entry point to initialize a PrintService

    After the PrintServiceProvider is connected, by using the AeviServiceProvider.connect(com.aevi.helpers.services.AeviServiceConnectionCallback) function, a AeviServiceConnectionCallback is returned containing the initialized service.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    PrintingServiceNotInstalledException
    Exception thrown when the underlying printing services are not installed.

Package com.aevi.printing Description

This package provides classes for printing functionality in third-party applications. When an application wants to initiate printing of a document, such as a receipt, it constructs a printing PrintPayload, comprising of the lines of the receipt, it binds to the PrintService via the PrintServiceProvider and issues the print command with the pay load as a parameter.
